        "assistant": "A **token substrate** is the underlying layer or medium that tokens are built on, represented in, or operate through.\n\nThe exact meaning depends on context:\n\n- **In blockchain/crypto:** a token substrate is the base blockchain or protocol that supports tokens.  \n  - Example: Ethereum is a substrate for ERC-20 tokens; Solana is a substrate for SPL tokens.\n  - It provides the rules for ownership, transfers, balances, and smart-contract execution.\n\n- **In AI/NLP:** a token substrate can mean the underlying representation system for text tokens.  \n  - Example: an LLM processes text as tokens, which are mapped into vectors/embeddings. That token-and-embedding layer can be thought of as the substrate the model operates on.\n\n- **More generally:** “substrate” means “underlying foundation,” so a token substrate is the foundation that gives tokens their structure, meaning, or functionality.\n\nSo, in simple terms: **a token substrate is the base system or layer that makes tokens possible and usable.**",
