        "user": "How does \"token substrate\" differ from context window?",
        "assistant": "A **token substrate** and a **context window** refer to different layers of how an AI model handles text.\n\n### Token substrate\n\nThe **token substrate** is the underlying system of tokens the model uses.\n\nIt includes:\n\n- The tokenizer\n- The vocabulary\n- Token IDs\n- Special tokens\n- Tokenization rules\n- The discrete token sequence format\n\nExample:\n\n```text\n\"Hello world\" → [\"Hello\", \" world\"] → [15496, 995]\n```\n\nThat tokenization system is part of the token substrate.\n\nIt defines **what counts as a token** and how text is converted into model-readable units.\n\n---\n\n### Context window\n\nThe **context window** is the maximum amount of tokenized input the model can consider at one time.\n\nFor example, if a model has a context window of 128,000 tokens, then the model can attend to up to 128,000 tokens in a single prompt/conversation segment.\n\nExample:\n\n```text\n[Token 1, Token 2, Token 3, ..., Token 128000]\n```\n\nIf the conversation exceeds that limit, older tokens may need to be removed, summarized, or ignored depending on the system.\n\n---\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | Token substrate | Context window |\n|---|---|---|\n| What it is | The token system itself | The amount of tokens the model can process at once |\n| Role | Defines the units | Defines the capacity limit |\n| Type | Structural/foundational | Operational/architectural |\n| Includes | Tokenizer, vocab, token IDs, special tokens | Maximum sequence length |\n| Example | `\"cat\"` → token ID `4719` | Model can read 8k, 32k, 128k tokens, etc. |\n\n---\n\n### Simple analogy\n\nIf the model is reading a book:\n\n- The **token substrate** is like the alphabet, words, and punctuation system.\n- The **context window** is like how many pages the model can keep open on its desk at once.\n\nSo:\n\n> The token substrate defines the units of text.  \n> The context window defines how many of those units can be considered at one time.",
